text: Géneviève Bogers (born 2 June 1997) is a Dutch martial arts fighter from Oosterbeek. She represents the Netherlands in ju-jitsu at international competitions. In 2018 she competed at the World Championships. Despite suffering from a shoulder injury, she finished in seventh position. At the 2021 World Championships, she won the bronze medal. She participated at the 2022 World Games, winning the bronze medal in the mixed team event. ==References== Category:1997 births Category:Living people Category:Sportswomen Category:Dutch martial artists
